Second systematic sweep (8 probes: $(eval)+foreach rule generation,
.SECONDEXPANSION, .DELETE_ON_ERROR, .ONESHELL, -k, %-rule chains with
.PRECIOUS, != / .SHELLSTATUS, -include remake chains). 4 passed
immediately; the other 4 were real divergences, all fixed:

- .SHELLSTATUS was set by $(shell) but not by `!=` shell assignment.
- `-include gen.inc` files with rules were never remade — only
  REQUIRED includes queued for the remake loop; GNU remakes optional
  ones too (missing + no rule stays tolerated). pending_remake_includes
  carries a required flag now.
- .SECONDEXPANSION worked only for explicit rules: a pattern rule's
  $$(deps_$$*) prereq (a) failed the implicit-rule viability probe as
  literal text — deferred when it contains '$' — and (b) expanded
  without the stem; $*, $(*D), $(*F) are now bound during second
  expansion, per the manual.
- -k was accepted-but-ignored: the executor now marks the failed
  node's transitive dependents not-remade and keeps building the rest,
  prints GNU's 'Target "X" not remade because of errors.' per failed
  goal, exits non-zero. Also honored from a makefile-level
  `MAKEFLAGS += -k` (read from the FINAL variable at exec time).

rkati corpus 395/405 fail=0 xpass=0; box corpus 395/405 fail=0.

